<subSubSection id="C368652E935D8E00F2AAFCF3FB2FFC54" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935D8E00F2AAFCF3FB2FFC54" blockId="4.[151,1436,865,1108]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935D8E00F2AAFCF3FB2BFC54" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147327" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
The specimen here recognized as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935D8E00F032FCF3FDA0FCB0" box="[527,625,865,891]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">holotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F182FCF0FBABFCB0" authority="Kollar" authorityName="Kollar" box="[959,1146,865,891]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F182FCF0FBFDFCB0" box="[959,1068,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">giganteus</emphasis>
Kollar
</taxonomicName>
in Hispania mer. in Cadix D”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935D8E00F3C3FC17FDB8FC54" box="[510,617,901,927]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F0B3FC14FBD6FC54" authority="Dejean, 1831" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" box="[654,1031,901,928]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F0B3FC14FCBBFC54" box="[654,874,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Acinopus giganteus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F14CFC17FBD6FC54" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[881,1031,901,927]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" refId="ref10829" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1831) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome cinquieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, viii + 883 pp." type="book" year="1831">Dejean, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935D8E00F647FC14FB21FC54" box="[1146,1264,901,928]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935D8E00F2FAFC38FDC2FB98" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935D8E00F2FAFC38FE0CFBC0" blockId="4.[151,1436,865,1108]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F2FAFC38FE72FC08" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" box="[199,419,938,964]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F2FAFC38FE72FC08" box="[199,419,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Acinopus giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently included in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F174FC38FC60FC0F" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[841,945,938,964]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F174FC38FC60FC0F" box="[841,945,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Acinopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and differs from other related species in the lack of punctures in elytron intervals 5 and 7, the lack of ventral pubescence on male protarsomeres forming two rows, and its large body size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935D8E00F2FAFB84FDC2FB98" blockId="4.[151,1436,865,1108]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">
It is solely known from 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F847935D8E00F3EEFB87FD94FBE4" box="[467,581,1045,1071]" country="Spain" name="Andalucia" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Andalusia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F069FB87FD27FBE4" author="Serrano, J." box="[596,758,1045,1071]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref12328" refString="Serrano, J. (2020) Catalogo electronico de los Cicindelidae y Carabidae de la Peninsula Iberica (Coleoptera, Caraboidea). [Version 12 - 2020]. Monografias electronicas Sociedad entomologica aragonesa (SEA), 9, 1 - 34. [http: // sea-entomologia. org / monoelec. html]" type="journal article" year="2020">Serrano, 2020</bibRefCitation>
), south of River Guadalquivir. Keys to the species are found in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F289FBA8FE83FB98" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[180,338,1081,1108]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente (1927)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F3B5FBABFDDEFB98" author="Puel, L." box="[392,527,1081,1107]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="70 - 86" refId="ref12096" refString="Puel, L. (1934) Notes sur les carabiques. IV. Les Acinopus palearctiques. Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, 1, 70 - 86." type="journal article" year="1934">Puel (1934)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
